        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="1125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1125">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.01/6–1745: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-23T20:00:00-04:00">June 23, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>174. Reurtel 239, June 17. In replying to the King’s communication re Syria and
                    Lebanon you should inform him of this Govt’s appreciation of his message and
                    assure him that careful note has been taken of his views in the matter. You may
                    add that this Govt will continue to work toward a settlement of the Levant
                    crisis which will take full account of the independence and sovereignty of Syria
                    and Lebanon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
